<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="494" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1677,2028]" pageId="7" pageNumber="494">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1714,1740]" pageId="7" pageNumber="494">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jewett, S. G." box="[655,821,1714,1740]" pageId="7" pageNumber="494" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref9121" refString="Jewett, S. G. (1960 b) Two new species of Anacroneuria (Plecoptera) from Goias, Brazil. Contributions in Science, 36, 1 - 4. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / p. 241035" type="journal article" year="1960">Jewett (1960b)</bibRefCitation>
based on specimens from the region of Formoso, in the north of Goiás state, BR. Similarly to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jewett" authorityYear="1960" box="[579,706,1750,1776]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="494" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dourada">
<emphasis box="[579,706,1750,1776]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="494">A. dourada</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, according to the original description the type series is deposited in the National Museum of Rio de Janeiro, RJ, BR (
<typeStatus box="[727,828,1786,1812]" pageId="7" pageNumber="494">holotype</typeStatus>
) and NHM, CA, 
<collectingCountry box="[1021,1075,1786,1812]" name="United States of America" pageId="7" pageNumber="494">USA</collectingCountry>
(
<typeStatus box="[1090,1204,1786,1812]" pageId="7" pageNumber="494">paratypes</typeStatus>
). However, the 
<typeStatus pageId="7" pageNumber="494">holotype</typeStatus>
is also currently lost. Fortunately, a dry preserved 
<typeStatus box="[774,870,1822,1848]" pageId="7" pageNumber="494">paratype</typeStatus>
is located in the NHM. The male 
<typeStatus box="[1257,1353,1822,1848]" pageId="7" pageNumber="494">paratype</typeStatus>
is well preserved. Its genitalia has not been dissected and there are no illustrations of the penial armature of the species. Therefore, the morphology of this 
<typeStatus box="[537,636,1894,1920]" pageId="7" pageNumber="494">paratype</typeStatus>
, including the morphology of the penial armature, needs to be carefully studied before trying to associate it with specimens collected in the type locality in north of Goiás state. The fact that the 
<typeStatus box="[193,289,1966,1992]" pageId="7" pageNumber="494">paratype</typeStatus>
is male can facilitate this process. The other specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jewett" authorityYear="1960" box="[960,1056,1966,1992]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="494" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="galba">
<emphasis box="[960,1056,1966,1992]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="494">A. galba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cited by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jewett, S. G." box="[1162,1330,1966,1992]" pageId="7" pageNumber="494" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref9121" refString="Jewett, S. G. (1960 b) Two new species of Anacroneuria (Plecoptera) from Goias, Brazil. Contributions in Science, 36, 1 - 4. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / p. 241035" type="journal article" year="1960">Jewett (1960b)</bibRefCitation>
for other localities (Espírito Santo, Minas Gerais, and São Paulo states) probably belong to other species (
<bibRefCitation author="Froehlich, C. G." box="[1230,1408,2002,2028]" pageId="7" pageNumber="494" pagination="118 - 205" refId="ref8981" refString="Froehlich, C. G. (2010) Catalogue of Neotropical Plecoptera. Illiesia, 6 (12), 118 - 205." type="journal article" year="2010">Froehlich 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
